<TITLE> Bangladesh take part in Grand Royal Challenge Cup in Myanmar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 28 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Football Federation (BFF) Tuesday decided to send the Under-23 team to the 3rd Grand Royal Challenge Cup to be held from November 1 to 7 in Yangon, Myanmar. "We Tuesday have decided to send our youth team to the Under-23 tournament Tuesday," said BFF acting general secretary Manjoor Hossain Malu adding that they would request the hosts to allow Bangladesh to send a few senior players with the youth side. Hosts Myanmar, Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Vietnam and Bangladesh are scheduled to take part in the six-nation tournament where Bangladesh emerged runners-up in the last edition in 2005. The Myanmar Football Federation on August 18 invited Bangladesh and sought confirmation of their participation by August 29. Malu said they are planning to send the footballers to Chittagong physical training centre for one month in a bid to strengthen their fitness and that he would visit Chittagong on the first week of September before sending a 30-member squad under the supervision of Indian coach Syed Nayeemuddin. 
